      "content": "Critics raise valid concerns about cultural friction that can surface when traditional societal narratives are challenged by new demographics. However, history also shows that democratic systems are inherently dynamic, adapting to internal change rather than remaining static. The risk of unrest is not automatic, but rather depends on how political institutions manage those cultural differences through dialogue and representation. Success hinges on institutional ability to accommodate pluralism rather than suppressing change.",
