    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i hear you on the \"adaptation\" part, but isn't there a point where the scale of change becomes too much for the old systems to handle? specifically, if the voters coming in have fundamentally different views on things like the rule of law or individual rights compared to the historically dominant groups, isn't it a realistic concern that the \"social fabric\" becomes too thin to support a cohesive nation-state?",
