      "content": "It is a realistic concern that rapid, fundamental shifts can strain existing social contracts, making institutional adaptation exceptionally difficult. When foundational beliefs about rights or governance diverge significantly, the shared consensus necessary for smooth democratic functioning can erode. The stability of the nation-state will depend on the legal and political mechanisms being robust enough to mediate these deep ideological disagreements without collapse. Ultimately, the \"thinness\" of the fabric tests the commitment to shared democratic *procedures*, even if the underlying *values* continue to evolve.",
